HEADWORD: Cormophyta
<hw>Cor*moph"y*ta</hw> <pr>(k⟦ocr⟧r*m⟦ocr⟧f"⟦icr⟧*t⟦adot⟧)</pr>,
}</mhw> <pos>n. pl.</pos> <ety>[NL. <ets>cormophyta</ets>, fr. Gr.
<grk>kormo`s</grk> trunk of a tree + <grk>fyto`n</grk> plant.]</ety>
<fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A term proposed by Endlicher to include all
plants with an axis containing vascular tissue and with
foliage.</def>⟦br⟧
